# Fixture: fm4-having-select-alias
# Finding: Failure Mode 4 — HAVING references SELECT aggregate alias
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §11.4, §11.4.2 (aggregate scope in HAVING)
# Errata: SE-3; public-sparql-dev "GROUP BY with expressions" (2013)
#
# Hypothesis: ?cnt is an alias for COUNT(?o) defined in the SELECT clause.
# SPARQL §11.4.2 allows HAVING to reference aggregate aliases from SELECT.
# An implementation that evaluates HAVING before projecting SELECT aliases
# will fail to resolve ?cnt, either producing a type error or treating it
# as unbound, causing wrong results.
#
# Divergence: HAVING evaluated before SELECT projection cannot see ?cnt;
# the HAVING clause is silently ignored or errors. Correct: HAVING sees
# the projected aggregate alias.
# Grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully.

SELECT (COUNT(?o) AS ?cnt) (SUM(?v) AS ?total)
WHERE {
  ?s <http://example/p> ?o ;
     <http://example/q> ?v .
}
GROUP BY ?s
HAVING (?cnt > 2)
